						               													<description>Global Mining was conceived and developed by real miners who are also fans of board games. It is a turn-based strategy game whose goal is to get the best result consisting in creating a global company dealing with the exploitation of all minerals and raw materials. The map of the main game is a map of the earth with a representation of actual resources. The game will be produced in 4 versions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Full Edition: 180 map tiles,&amp;#10;     North and South America: 60 map tiles.&amp;#10;     Europe and Africa: 60 map tiles.&amp;#10;     Asia and Australia: 60 map tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each edition will contain a basic set of pawns for each player: Geologist, Mine, Pipeline, Seaport, Railroad, Oil Rig and a proportional number of resource pawns: Oil Barrels, Gas Barrels, Coal, Gold, Silver, Copper, Iron Ore, Rare Earth Metals, Nickel, Magnesite, Stone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Global Mining is a turn-based game, the winner is the player who scores the most points within a certain time. Points are earned by: discovering natural resources such as Gold, building mines, building pipelines, building railways, building seaports, establishing transport lines for ships.&amp;#10;Global Mining is based on linguistically universal symbols. The game manual in the first edition will be translated into: Polish, English, German, Spanish, French, Czech.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
